Christopher Williams is Founder and Executive Director of Heart, Body & Soul, Inc., a  Brooklyn based nonprofit and the creator of “The Black Man’s Health Festival”, which he  launched June 4, 2022 to focus on Black Men’s Health Awareness initiatives. A resident  of Brooklyn, Christopher experienced a number of personal health issues including two  heart attacks and a diagnosis of stage III appendiceal cancer, which forever changed his  path and redefined his purpose.  When asked why he developed HBS, Christopher had this to say - “Limited access to  quality healthcare and poor health outcomes are huge issues in the Black community and  unfortunately due to the healthcare disparities that exist, including lack of access to quality  wellness programs, health education and so on, Black men are less likely to get annual  check-ups, seek mental health services or share their challenges with others. Whether it’s  cultural, psychological or generational, the fact remains that open and honest conversations  about health need to be had and it needs to happen frequently among Black men.” Christopher is also Associate Publisher and co-founder of WhereItzAt Magazine, a NYC  based, family-owned media company that has served the New York City community for  over 19 years. Christopher has over 25 years of experience in media, financial services,  recruitment and project management. Christopher began his career as a radio engineer  alongside his father, who mentored him in the media and communications industry. Later,  Christopher started his corporate career at Salomon Smith Barney in equity research and  since then has held various roles in the private and public sector. Christopher continues to provide expertise as a consultant in the areas of media and event  production, but his primary focus today remains advocating for a change in the way Black  men address their own mental and physical health challenges and work towards improving their outcomes.

Walter is a transformative leader with a superpower of helping people and organizations get to their desired future faster. To do so he deploys skills in organizational and program management, strategy creation and execution, objective setting and reporting, team building as well as culture curation.  Empowering it all, is the ability to connect and motivate people around causes, objectives and initiatives through storytelling with data.  These abilities have helped him lead over 10k hours' worth of impactful projects and programs for organizations like MorganFranklin Consulting & CapitalOne, design strategy gaming scenarios for financial institutions like UBS and Bank of America, help fintech startup TiiCKER raise over 2M in pre-seed funding, launch now failed ed-tech startup The Mobile Business School and lead as a senior leader through one of the fastest and largest bank failures in US History at Silicon Valley Bank.  Walter is a member of the National Black MBA Association and has helped facilitate leadership development workshops for young men and young professionals via the Men of Courage program sponsored by the Ford Foundation, the United Negro College Fund's Koch Scholar Program and the young leaders' program of the Detroit Economic Club.  Walter has an MBA from Emory University's Goizueta Business School in Atlanta and a bachelors in advertising from Michigan State University. When he is not working, Walter loves to travel and is an amateur DJ.

I have a robust background leading the People and Culture function and supporting executive leadership teams. As a proactive driver of business and organizational strategies, I have successfully crafted and executed HR initiatives aligning seamlessly with company objectives. My expertise extends to the future of work, onboarding, and succession planning, particularly in hyper-growth startups and Fortune 100 companies.   Recognized for steering talent strategies through periods of rapid expansion, I bring a wealth of knowledge in optimizing organizational effectiveness and fostering success in evolving work landscapes. Poised to leverage this experience and expertise to drive transformative talent management initiatives in your organization.  Over the last 15 years, I’ve led cross-functional teams and spearheaded company-wide initiatives, shaping robust policies and strategies that significantly bolstered employee retention. My focus encompassed refining company policies, internal communications, learning and development, as well as onboarding and compliance, all in support of a comprehensive people operations framework.  In the C-Suite, I wear the hat of a trusted advisor and a transparent collaborator to our esteemed CEO and leadership team. I champion a culture of openness, where direct and honest feedback fuels our collective success. I am a Fractional HR Innovapreneur. (PS Consulting, Founder)  In the realm of leadership, I lead by example. My philosophy is simple—credibility is earned through effective decision-making, appreciating exceptional work, and making those tough calls when necessary. Accountability is my anchor, fostering a culture of ownership and collaboration.  Recognized as a top 100 DEIB leader of 2022 by Untapped, I have made it my mission to share my knowledge and experiences through various mediums. From DEI to Performance, Learning & Development, and Talent Management, I've poured my insights into the world. You can find my articles on DEI, teamwork , remote work and leadership gracing the digital pages of Medium. I am that dependable glue that holds the team together, driven by curiosity, creativity, and resourcefulness.  On a lighter note, I'm an avid reader, a jazz aficionado, and a die-hard fan of Golden Girls and Seinfeld. I am into physical challenges, like Tough Mudder. If you share a passion for HGTV's House Hunters, you may have seen me. I am passionate about community service.    I extend an invitation to you all to connect with me.  Let's discuss how I can infuse your organization with a robust people strategy.
